        <div xml:id="Kali60-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">itu talaimakaṟkuk kuṟainērnta tōḻi talaimakaḷōṭu uṟaḻntu avaṉatu kuṟainayappak kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"/>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="Kali60">
            <lg type="edition">
                <l>cuṇaṅkaṇi vaṉamulaic cuṭarkoṇṭa naṟunutaṉ</l>
                <l>maṇaṅkamaḻ naṟuṅkōtai mārivī ḻiruṅkūnta</l>
                <l>ṉuṇaṅkeḻi loṇṭitti nuḻainoci maṭamaruṅkul</l>
                <l>vaṇaṅkiṟai varimuṉkai variyārnta valkulāy;</l>
                <l rend="space">kaṇṇārnta nalattāraik katumeṉak kaṇṭavark</l>
                <l>kuṇṇiṉṟa nōymika vuyireñcu tuyarceytal,</l>
                <l>peṇṇaṉṟu puṉaiyiḻā yeṉakkūṟit toḻūun toḻutē,</l>
                <l>kaṇṇunī rāka naṭuṅkiṉa ṉiṉṉakā</l>
                <l>yeṉceytāṉ kollō viḵtottaṉ ṟaṉkaṭ</l>
                <l>porukaḷi ṟaṉṉa takaicāmpi yuḷḷu</l>
                <l>ḷurukuvāṉ pōlu muṭaintu;</l>
                <l rend="space">teruviṉkaṇ, kāraṇa miṉṟik kalaṅkuvārk kaṇṭunī</l>
                <l>vāraṇa vācip patampeyarta lētila</l>
                <l>nīniṉmēṟ koḷva tevaṉ;</l>
                <l rend="space">alarmulai yāyiḻai nallāy katumeṉap</l>
                <l>pērama ruṇkaṇeṉ ṟōḻi yuṟīiya</l>
                <l>vāraña revva muyirvāṅku</l>
                <l>maṟṟinnōy tīru maruntaruḷā yoṇṭoṭī;</l>
                <l rend="space">niṉmukaṅ kāṇu maruntiṉē ṉeṉṉumā</l>
                <l>ṉiṉmukan tāṉpeṟi ṉallatu koṉṉē</l>
                <l>maruntu piṟitiyātu millēṟ ṟiruntiḻā</l>
                <l>yeṉceyvāṅ kolliṉi nām;</l>
                <l rend="space">poṉceyvām,</l>
                <l>āṟu vilaṅkit teruviṉka ṇiṉṟoruvaṉ</l>
                <l>kūṟuñcol vāyeṉak koṇṭataṉ paṇpuṇarān</l>
                <l>tēṟa leḷiteṉpā nām;</l>
                <l rend="space">oruvaṉ, cāmā ṟeḷiteṉpā maṟṟu;</l>
                <l rend="space">ciṟitāṅkē, māṇāvū rampa lalari ṉalarkeṉa</l>
                <l>nāṇu niṟaiyu nayappil piṟappili</l>
                <l>pūṇāka nōkki yimaiyā ṉayantunaṅ</l>
                <l>kēṇmai viruppuṟ ṟavaṉai yetirniṉṟu</l>
                <l>nāṇaṭap peyartta nayavara viṉṟē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>            You with beautiful breasts adorned with beauty spots, with a glowing fragrant forehead,</l>
<l>with a fragrant garland scented with perfume, with dark tresses that descend [like] clouds,</l>
<l>with a thin innocent(?) belly onto which got fine graceful bright beauty spots,</l>
<l>with flexible joints, lined forearms [and] hips that are full of lines:</l>
<l rend="space">“Causing misery that diminishes life, so that pain abounds which stays inside</l>
<l>to those who see fleetingly(?) good girls of whom [their] eyes are full</l>
<l>is not woman[-like], you with ornate jewels”, telling [you this] he worships [you] intently.</l>
<l>He shivered, [his] eyes becoming [all] water, you with a sweet smile.</l>
<l>What has he done? He is like this.</l>
<l>Broken, it seems he will melt </l>
<l>all inside, [his] fitness whithering like [that of] the elephant that fought him.</l>
<l rend="space">In the street, seeing those who are stirred up without reason, you</l>
<l>strangely moving at the right moment to Varānasi </l>
<l>what is it you have taken upon yourself?</l>
<l rend="space">Good one with choice jewels on [your] blooming breasts, quickly</l>
<l>grant the remedy that will end this pain</l>
<l>that pulls at the life with the trouble of difficult grief</l>
<l>which you caused, my friend with big beautiful kajal eyes, o you with bright bracelets.</l>
<l rend="space">If he says “I am one for whom the remedy will be seeing your face,</l>
<l>unless if he obtains your face, futilely,</l>
<l>if there is no other remedy at all, you with perfect jewels,</l>
<l>what shall we do now?</l>
<l rend="space">We shall doing nothing.</l>
<l rend="space">Someone, standing in the street, right across [our] way,</l>
<l>the word he speaks, taking it for true whe don’t understand its impact.</l>
<l>Understanding is easy we say.</l>
<l rend="space">Else, we say it is an easy way to die for [that] someone.</l>
<l rend="space">He is without birth, with no love for [my] shame and self-control/fulness,</l>
<l>saying “let rumour bloom like a flower in [this] inglorious village”, a little like that.</l>
<l rend="space">Standing opposite one who feels the desire for intimacy with us,</l>
<l>longing, one who does not blink when looking at [our] ornate bosom,</l>
<l>there is no starting the longing that is dislodged so that shame kills.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
